So, here you are.

1219
01:15:20,795 --> 01:15:22,737
M-M-M-Mr. Scrooge.

1220
01:15:23,099 --> 01:15:26,165
You, sir, were not at work this morning
as we had discussed.

1221
01:15:26,235 --> 01:15:28,919
But, Mr. Scrooge, sir,
we did discuss it.

1222
01:15:28,988 --> 01:15:31,159
It's Christmas Day.
You gave me the day off.

1223
01:15:31,227 --> 01:15:32,274
I?

1224
01:15:32,347 --> 01:15:34,714
I, Ebenezer Scrooge?

1225
01:15:34,779 --> 01:15:36,568
- Would I do a thing like that?
- No.

1226
01:15:36,635 --> 01:15:38,326
I mean, yes, but you did.

1227
01:15:38,396 --> 01:15:40,283
Bob Cratchit, I've had my fill of this.

1228
01:15:40,348 --> 01:15:42,998
And I have had my fill of you,
Mr. Scrooge.

1229
01:15:43,067 --> 01:15:44,561
And therefore, Bob Cratchit...

1230
01:15:44,635 --> 01:15:46,937
And therefore,
you can leave this house at once.

1231
01:15:47,003 --> 01:15:49,272
And therefore,
I'm about to raise your salary.

1232
01:15:49,339 --> 01:15:53,016
And I am about to raise you
right off the pavement...

1233
01:15:53,083 --> 01:15:54,131
- Pardon?
- Pardon?

1234
01:15:54,204 --> 01:15:55,611
Yes, Bob.

1235
01:15:55,676 --> 01:15:57,269
Raise your salary.

1236
01:15:57,340 --> 01:16:00,154
And pay your mortgage
on this house.

1237
01:16:01,915 --> 01:16:03,737
Please, sir, come inside.

1238
01:16:03,804 --> 01:16:05,014
Yes, yes.

1239
01:16:05,083 --> 01:16:08,280
Bob Cratchit, would you and your family
care to join us

1240
01:16:08,348 --> 01:16:11,828
for a little turkey dinner
on this fine Christmas Day?

1241
01:16:11,899 --> 01:16:13,808
Merry Christmas.

1242
01:16:23,516 --> 01:16:25,850
[Dickens] And Scrooge
was better than his word.

1243
01:16:25,915 --> 01:16:28,533
He did it all, and infinitely more.

1244
01:16:28,603 --> 01:16:30,426
And, er, Tiny Tim?

1245
01:16:30,491 --> 01:16:31,985
And Tiny Tim,

1246
01:16:32,059 --> 01:16:33,619
who did not die...

1247
01:16:33,691 --> 01:16:35,153
Isn't that swell?

1248
01:16:35,227 --> 01:16:38,359
To Tiny Tim,
Scrooge became a second father.

1249
01:16:38,427 --> 01:16:40,979
He became as good a friend,
as good a master,

1250
01:16:41,051 --> 01:16:44,662
and as good a man
as the good old city ever had.

1251
01:16:44,731 --> 01:16:47,666
It was always said of him that
he knew how to keep Christmas well,

1252
01:16:47,739 --> 01:16:50,008
if any man alive
possessed the knowledge.

1253
01:16:50,076 --> 01:16:54,134
May that truly be said of us
and all of us.

1254
